Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.19,0:02:09.66,1080P_CN_Up,,0,1000,0,,齐奥尔科夫斯基环形山\NЦиолковский
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.19,0:02:09.66,1080P_CN_Up,,1000,0,0,,莫斯科海\NМоре Москвы
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.24,0:04:47.88,1080P_CN_Up,,0,0,0,,字幕翻译给虫，欢迎点赞投币收藏分享转发评论关注充电~
Dialogue: 1,0:00:02.52,0:00:07.88,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,这是阿波罗11号——人类历史上第一次登月的画面
Dialogue: 2,0:00:02.52,0:00:07.88,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,This is Apollo 11, landing on the Moon for the first time in human history.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:09.10,0:00:12.88,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,着陆后几秒钟，尼尔·阿姆斯特朗说
Dialogue: 2,0:00:09.10,0:00:12.88,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Just a few seconds after touchdown, Neil Armstrong said
Dialogue: 1,0:00:13.24,0:00:16.52,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,“这里是静海基地。‘鹰’着陆成功。”
Dialogue: 2,0:00:13.24,0:00:16.52,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,“Tranquility Base here, the Eagle has landed”.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:17.22,0:00:21.98,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,静海基地是NASA选择作为人类首次登月的着陆地点
Dialogue: 2,0:00:17.22,0:00:21.98,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Tranquility Base was the name that NASA had chosen for the site of the first Moon landing.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:22.54,0:00:28.27,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,它位于月球平原“静海”的西南角
Dialogue: 2,0:00:22.54,0:00:28.27,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,It’s located in the south-western corner of the Lunar plain called Mare Tranquillitatis
Dialogue: 1,0:00:28.27,0:00:30.30,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,意为“宁静之海”
Dialogue: 2,0:00:28.27,0:00:30.30,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,or “Sea of Tranquility”.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:31.27,0:00:36.32,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,它只是月球上千个以其地理学特点命名的名字之一
Dialogue: 2,0:00:31.27,0:00:36.32,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,This is just one out of thousands of names that have been given to geographical features on the Moon.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:36.92,0:00:39.90,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,那这名字是谁钦定的？
Dialogue: 2,0:00:36.92,0:00:39.90,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,But who is in charge of coming up with these names?
Dialogue: 1,0:00:39.90,0:00:41.04,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,是官方名字吗？
Dialogue: 2,0:00:39.90,0:00:41.04,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,And are they official?
Dialogue: 1,0:00:41.98,0:00:46.28,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,本期视频我们就来学习一个如何给月球地点命名
Dialogue: 2,0:00:41.98,0:00:46.28,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,In this video we’re going to look at how we began naming features on the Moon.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:46.29,0:00:50.40,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,我们还将了解谁负责让名字成为官方名称
Dialogue: 2,0:00:46.29,0:00:50.40,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,We’re also going to look at who’s in charge of making these names official
Dialogue: 1,0:00:50.40,0:00:53.80,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,以及为月球地名命名的严格规则
Dialogue: 2,0:00:50.40,0:00:53.80,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,and the strict rules around naming a place on the Moon.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:55.34,0:00:59.90,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,1610年，伽利略公布了他著名的月球画像
Dialogue: 2,0:00:55.34,0:00:59.90,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,In the year 1610, Galileo released his famous drawings of the Moon.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:00.62,0:01:05.25,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,利用世界上第一架望远镜，他能更“近距离”研究月球
Dialogue: 2,0:01:00.62,0:01:05.25,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Looking through one of the world’s very first telescopes, he studied the moon closely
Dialogue: 1,0:01:05.25,0:01:09.78,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,并能够对月球画像以准确表现月球崎岖不平的表面
Dialogue: 2,0:01:05.25,0:01:09.78,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,and was able to produce drawings which accurately represented the Moon’s harsh features
Dialogue: 1,0:01:09.78,0:01:12.60,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,而这种方法其他人从未做过
Dialogue: 2,0:01:09.78,0:01:12.60,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,in a way that no one else had ever seen before.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:13.50,0:01:16.90,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,虽然伽利略绘制出第一份月球地图
Dialogue: 2,0:01:13.50,0:01:16.90,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Although Galileo had essentially created the very first map of the Moon,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:17.20,0:01:19.34,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,但地图上却没标地名
Dialogue: 2,0:01:17.20,0:01:19.34,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,there were no place names on this map.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:20.30,0:01:25.76,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,40年后，天文学家里乔利和格里马尔迪绘制了一份新的月球地图
Dialogue: 2,0:01:20.30,0:01:25.76,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,40 years later, a new map of the Moon was created by astronomers Riccioli and Grimaldi.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:26.04,0:01:29.02,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,这份地图将月球分成8块区域
Dialogue: 2,0:01:26.04,0:01:29.02,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,This map divided the Moon up into 8 sections
Dialogue: 1,0:01:29.08,0:01:35.80,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,而每块区域中的高山、平原则被命名为“宁静”、“澄净”等
Dialogue: 2,0:01:29.08,0:01:35.80,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,and names like ‘Tranquility’ and ‘Serenity’ were given to the great mountains and flat plains that lay in between.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:36.69,0:01:43.66,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,该地图很快变成月球地名命名基础，其中好多名字沿用至今
Dialogue: 2,0:01:36.69,0:01:43.66,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,This map quickly became the basis for naming the Moon’s features and many of the original names are still used to this day.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:44.69,0:01:48.46,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,几个世纪后，人类航天事业正式起步
Dialogue: 2,0:01:44.69,0:01:48.46,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Fast forward by a few centuries and we have the birth of spaceflight.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:49.26,0:01:55.12,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,1959年，苏联第一次把探测器送到月球背面
Dialogue: 2,0:01:49.26,0:01:55.12,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,In 1959, the Soviets became the first to send a probe to the far side of the moon.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:55.80,0:02:01.02,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,它让人类首次看到月球背面的画面
Dialogue: 2,0:01:55.80,0:02:01.02,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,This probe successfully imaged the side of the Moon which had never been seen before by humans.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:01.86,0:02:04.50,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,有了月球背面的画面
Dialogue: 2,0:02:01.86,0:02:04.50,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,With this new perspective of the Moon’s hidden surface,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:04.50,0:02:09.13,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,苏联开始用他们的英雄和地名为月球上的地方命名
Dialogue: 2,0:02:04.50,0:02:09.13,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,the Soviets started to name features after Russian Heroes and place names.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:09.88,0:02:16.80,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,之后十年，美苏两国开始收集大量更清晰的月球背面照片
Dialogue: 2,0:02:09.88,0:02:16.80,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Over the next decade, America and The Soviets started to piece together higher quality images of the far side of the Moon
Dialogue: 1,0:02:16.80,0:02:20.20,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,并为新地名命名
Dialogue: 2,0:02:16.80,0:02:20.20,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,whilst continuing to name newly found features.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:20.98,0:02:24.28,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,虽然NASA经常给月球添加非正式地名
Dialogue: 2,0:02:20.98,0:02:24.28,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Although NASA often informally names features on the Moon,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:24.28,0:02:29.14,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,但他们根本没有权力去正式给月球上的地名命名
Dialogue: 2,0:02:24.28,0:02:29.14,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,they don’t actually have any authority to officially assign names to lunar features.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:29.70,0:02:32.72,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,当为其他星球的地名命名时
Dialogue: 2,0:02:29.70,0:02:32.72,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,When naming features on other planetary bodies,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:32.72,0:02:37.32,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,每个名字都必须被国际天文联合会接受
Dialogue: 2,0:02:32.72,0:02:37.32,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,each name has to be accepted by the International Astronomical Union.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:37.84,0:02:44.18,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,但不止有NASA，任何人都可以向IAU提交命名
Dialogue: 2,0:02:37.84,0:02:44.18,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,However, it’s not just NASA that can suggest names, anyone can submit a name to the IAU
Dialogue: 1,0:02:44.34,0:02:47.20,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,只要其符合他们的一些特定的原则
Dialogue: 2,0:02:44.34,0:02:47.20,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,as long as it complies with their specific guidelines.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:47.82,0:02:53.09,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,月球上的环形山(陨石坑)必须以已故科学家、探险家的名字命名
Dialogue: 2,0:02:47.82,0:02:53.09,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Almost all craters on the Moon must be named after deceased scientists or explorers who
Dialogue: 1,0:02:53.09,0:02:55.66,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,且他们必须在自己的领域有过杰出贡献
Dialogue: 2,0:02:53.09,0:02:55.66,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,have made a significant contribution to their field.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:56.39,0:03:00.78,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,月球上大平原之类的地名必须起拉丁文名字
Dialogue: 2,0:02:56.39,0:03:00.78,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,The large plains that are so common on the Moon must be given Latin names
Dialogue: 1,0:03:00.78,0:03:04.62,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,意义必须是类似天气等的抽象概念
Dialogue: 2,0:03:00.78,0:03:04.62,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,which describe things like weather and other abstract concepts.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:05.24,0:03:10.14,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,月球上发现的山脊之类，必须以地球科学家的名字命名
Dialogue: 2,0:03:05.24,0:03:10.14,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Ridges like these which are found on the Moon have to be named specifically after Geoscientists.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:10.68,0:03:15.36,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,虽然这些名字可能和科学界很多著名人士有关
Dialogue: 2,0:03:10.68,0:03:15.36,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Although these names may be attached to significant people within the science community,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:15.60,0:03:20.10,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,但其大小一般反映不出命名者的科学贡献大小
Dialogue: 2,0:03:15.60,0:03:20.10,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,the scale of a Lunar feature doesn’t necessarily reflect who it’s named after.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:20.54,0:03:26.58,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,哥白尼和阿基米德环形山在月球上都非常大
Dialogue: 2,0:03:20.54,0:03:26.58,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Copernicus and Archimedes both have their names attached to spectacularly large craters,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:26.76,0:03:33.28,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,但其他科学界传奇人物比如伽利略、牛顿这些名字的环形山则很小
Dialogue: 2,0:03:26.76,0:03:33.28,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,whereas other science legends like Galileo and Newton were given features that are much less impressive.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:34.86,0:03:40.96,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,在1970年，IAU同意将月球最大的环形山之一命名为“阿波罗环形山”
Dialogue: 2,0:03:34.86,0:03:40.96,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,In 1970, the IAU agreed to name one of the widest craters on the Moon ‘Apollo’
Dialogue: 1,0:03:41.14,0:03:47.10,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,而阿波罗环形山中的小环形山则用阿波罗8、11号宇航员的名字命名
Dialogue: 2,0:03:41.14,0:03:47.10,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,and smaller craters within Apollo were named after astronauts from the Apollo 8 and Apollo 11 missions.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:47.76,0:03:52.26,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,附近的环形山也在之后用NASA已故员工命名
Dialogue: 2,0:03:47.76,0:03:52.26,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Nearby craters were later named after deceased NASA employees,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:52.40,0:03:56.62,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,其中包括阿波罗1号、两架航天飞机灾难中丧生的宇航员
Dialogue: 2,0:03:52.40,0:03:56.62,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,including the lost crew of Apollo 1 and the two Space Shuttle disasters.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:57.76,0:04:01.30,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,虽然现在这些名字我们大多不认识
Dialogue: 2,0:03:57.76,0:04:01.30,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,So although these names might not be familiar to us now,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:01.62,0:04:04.72,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,当未来太空旅行成为现实的时候
Dialogue: 2,0:04:01.62,0:04:04.72,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,in the future when space tourism is a reality,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:04.94,0:04:13.22,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}阿波罗、博尔曼、洛弗尔这些地名或许会和纽约、巴黎、东京一样家喻户晓
Dialogue: 2,0:04:04.94,0:04:13.22,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,places like Apollo, Borman and Lovell might be as common to us as New York, Paris and Tokyo.
